nd\nkinetic parameters of the SLSP model are determined based on the lower level\nsimulation models. Particularly, matching the orientational autocorrelation of\nthe end-to-end vector, we determine the number of slip-springs and calibrate\nthe timescale of the SLSP model. As the test case, the hierarchical methodology\nis applied to $cis$-1,4-polybutadiene (cPB) at 413 K. Dynamical properties of\ncPB melts are calculated for a broad range of molecular weights. The\ncalculations are compared, and found in good agreement, with experimental data\nfrom the literature.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 22 Jan 2021 07:47:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-09"}
